### Pattern 7: All Import Paths Used by `@api/platform` Consumers

```
# Root import (router, context, JWT)
from "@api/platform"
  → apps/platform/src/app/(trpc)/api/trpc/[trpc]/route.ts
  → packages/platform-trpc/src/caller.ts
  → packages/platform-trpc/src/server.tsx
  → packages/platform-trpc/src/types.ts (type-only)

# Subpath imports
from "@api/platform/inngest"
  → apps/platform/src/app/api/inngest/route.ts

from "@api/platform/inngest/client"
  → apps/platform/src/app/api/ingest/[provider]/route.ts
  → packages/app-test-data/src/trigger/trigger.ts

from "@api/platform/lib/oauth/callback"
  → apps/platform/src/app/api/connect/[provider]/callback/route.ts

from "@api/platform/lib/oauth/authorize"
  → apps/platform/src/app/api/connect/[provider]/authorize/route.ts

from "@api/platform/lib/oauth/state"
  → apps/platform/src/app/api/connect/oauth/poll/route.ts

from "@api/platform/lib/provider-configs"
  → apps/platform/src/app/api/ingest/[provider]/route.ts
```

The `lib/oauth/*` and `lib/provider-configs` paths are used by `apps/platform` route handlers but are **not declared in `@api/platform`'s `exports` field** — they are accessed directly via the `node-linker=hoisted` workspace resolution (which bypasses subpath exports enforcement for internal packages).

